Pm-7pBRcM9DfzRurdfzx5iLiHvXjFPHdEmOP8nJ9R41sndczUw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing version compatibility**\\n\\nI’m checking if the active dynamic report after testing can track scala-reflect 2.13 and cover the same class. It could be alright, but there’s a concern because the current coordinate specifies version 2.11.8. That difference makes me wonder if there might be compatibility issues. I guess I need to clarify which version is being referenced to ensure everything aligns properly. It's a bit tricky, but I’ll figure it out!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Gradle setup**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the Gradle Scala plugin with zinc version 2.11 is necessary. It seems like sticking with the existing hardcoded version 2.13 might be intentional. Maybe I should focus on running the tests only for now. I need to think about removing any placeholders in the code as well. I'll go ahead and use the write method to proceed with these changes.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZYQJ9e2o9wpwLOWj4PPkPBDP|fc_00fbe55c2a84c5560169fa3b816ff081928657c3a8805ca8ff", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-reflect/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_reflect/JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_scala_lang.scala_reflect\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.MethodSymbol\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.TermName\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.TermSymbol\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.Type\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.runtimeMirror\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.termNames\n\nclass JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorTest {\n  @Test\n  def runtimeMirrorLoadsTopLevelJavaAndScalaSymbols(): Unit = {\n    val mirror = runtimeMirror(getClass.getClassLoader)\n\n    val stringSymbol = mirror.staticClass(\"java.lang.String\")\n    val optionSymbol = mirror.staticClass(\"scala.Option\")\n\n    assertThat(stringSymbol.fullName).isEqualTo(\"java.lang.String\")\n    assertThat(optionSymbol.fullName).isEqualTo(\"scala.Option\")\n    assertThat(optionSymbol.toType.decls.exists(_.name.toString == \"isEmpty\")).isTrue()\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def reflectsNestedClassConstructorsFieldsAndMethods(): Unit = {\n    val mirror = runtimeMirror(getClass.getClassLoader)\n    val nestedClassSymbol = mirror.staticClass(\n      \"org_scala_lang.scala_reflect.JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorFixtures.Nested\"\n    )\n    val nestedType = nestedClassSymbol.toType\n    val constructor = singleMethod(nestedType, termNames.CONSTRUCTOR)\n    val classMirror = mirror.reflectClass(nestedClassSymbol)\n\n    val nested = classMirror.reflectConstructor(constructor)(\"alpha\", 7)\n      .asInstanceOf[JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorFixtures.Nested]\n    val instanceMirror = mirror.reflect(nested)\n\n    val publicField = instanceMirror.reflectField(singleTerm(nestedType, TermName(\"publicValue\")))\n    assertThat(publicField.get.asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\"alpha\")\n\n    val publicMethod = instanceMirror.reflectMethod(singleMethod(nestedType, TermName(\"combine\")))\n    assertThat(publicMethod(\"id\").asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\"id:alpha:7\")\n\n    val packageScopedField = instanceMirror.reflectField(singleTerm(nestedType, TermName(\"packageScopedValue\")))\n    assertThat(packageScopedField.get.asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\"package-alpha\")\n    packageScopedField.set(\"changed\")\n    assertThat(nested.packageScopedSnapshot).isEqualTo(\"changed\")\n\n    val packageScopedMethod = instanceMirror.reflectMethod(singleMethod(nestedType, TermName(\"packageScopedMethod\")))\n    assertThat(packageScopedMethod(\"suffix\").asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\"changed-suffix\")\n  }\n\n  private def singleTerm(ownerType: Type, name: TermName): TermSymbol =\n    ownerType.decl(name).asTerm\n\n  private def singleMethod(ownerType: Type, name: TermName): MethodSymbol =\n    ownerType.decl(name).asMethod\n}\n\nobject JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorFixtures {\n  class Nested(var publicValue: String, val count: Int) {\n    private[scala_reflect] var packageScopedValue: String = s\"package-$publicValue\"\n\n    def combine(prefix: String): String = s\"$prefix:$publicValue:$count\"\n\n    private[scala_reflect] def packageScopedMethod(suffix: String): String = s\"$packageScopedValue-$suffix\"\n\n    def packageScopedSnapshot: String = packageScopedValue\n  }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-reflect/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_reflect/JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorTest.scala\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_scala_lang.scala_reflect\\n\\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.MethodSymbol\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.TermName\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.TermSymbol\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.Type\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.runtimeMirror\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe.termNames\\n\\nclass JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def runtimeMirrorLoadsTopLevelJavaAndScalaSymbols(): Unit = {\\n    val mirror = runtimeMirror(getClass.getClassLoader)\\n\\n    val stringSymbol = mirror.staticClass(\\\"java.lang.String\\\")\\n    val optionSymbol = mirror.staticClass(\\\"scala.Option\\\")\\n\\n    assertThat(stringSymbol.fullName).isEqualTo(\\\"java.lang.String\\\")\\n    assertThat(optionSymbol.fullName).isEqualTo(\\\"scala.Option\\\")\\n    assertThat(optionSymbol.toType.decls.exists(_.name.toString == \\\"isEmpty\\\")).isTrue()\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def reflectsNestedClassConstructorsFieldsAndMethods(): Unit = {\\n    val mirror = runtimeMirror(getClass.getClassLoader)\\n    val nestedClassSymbol = mirror.staticClass(\\n      \\\"org_scala_lang.scala_reflect.JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorFixtures.Nested\\\"\\n    )\\n    val nestedType = nestedClassSymbol.toType\\n    val constructor = singleMethod(nestedType, termNames.CONSTRUCTOR)\\n    val classMirror = mirror.reflectClass(nestedClassSymbol)\\n\\n    val nested = classMirror.reflectConstructor(constructor)(\\\"alpha\\\", 7)\\n      .asInstanceOf[JavaMirrorsInnerJavaMirrorFixtures.Nested]\\n    val instanceMirror = mirror.reflect(nested)\\n\\n    val publicField = instanceMirror.reflectField(singleTerm(nestedType, TermName(\\\"publicValue\\\")))\\n    assertThat(publicField.get.asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\\\"alpha\\\")\\n\\n    val publicMethod = instanceMirror.reflectMethod(singleMethod(nestedType, TermName(\\\"combine\\\")))\\n    assertThat(publicMethod(\\\"id\\\").asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\\\"id:alpha:7\\\")\\n\\n    val packageScopedField = instanceMirror.reflectField(singleTerm(nestedType, TermName(\\\"packageScopedValue\\\")))\\n    assertThat(packageScopedField.get.asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\\\"package-alpha\\\")\\n    packageScopedField.set(\\\"changed\\\")\\n    assertThat(nested.packageScopedSnapshot).isEqualTo(\\\"changed\\\")\\n\\n    val packageScopedMethod = instanceMirror.reflectMethod(singleMethod(nestedType, TermName(\\\"packageScopedMethod\\\")))\\n    assertThat(packageScopedMethod(\\\"suffix\\\").asInstanceOf[String]).isEqualTo(\\\"changed-suffix\\\")\\n  }\\n\\n  private def singleTerm(ownerType: Type, name: TermName): TermSymbol =\\n    ownerType.decl(name).asTerm\\n\\n  private def singleMethod(ownerType: Type, name: TermName): MethodSymbol =\\n    ownerType.decl(name).asMethod\\n}\\n\\nobject JavaM