[thinking] I'm considering how private members in Scala have their names expanded to avoid name collisions. For instance, if I have a private[this] variable x, the field name could just be x. But for a regular private variable, it might include an accessor, so the field could also be x. There's something interesting about how this can map Java names to Scala's private names. I wonder how it looks in bytecode if methods are kept private.
